Networking commands

tcpdump  : to capture packets 
eg:
  interface :
  
  sudo tcpdump -c 10 -i en0  (interface en0 - captured)
  
  for ports:
  
  sudo tcpdump -c 10 -etho port 22 (ssh connections to the ethernet  port 0)
    
  netstat
  
  network connections listing 
  
  netstat -nr 
  netstat -ta
  
  host file 
  
  /etc/hosts  : where the host look up for the address / you can provide addressess there to route
  
  traceroute
